<div id="middlecolumn1"><div class="multipageheading"><h1>Welcome to&nbsp;<strong>Social Issues</strong></h1><div class="multipagegraphic"><img width="70" height="70" src="/shared/graphics/kmbc/images/socialissues.gif" alt="Logotype for Social Issues" /></div>
</div>
<h2 class="subhead">Knowsley Against Racism</h2><div style="clear:both;"><ul><li>Racism is a serious crime that has a 
major effect on people&#039;s lives.</li>
<li>Too often this crime is ignored.</li>
<li>This is where it stops.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div style="clear:both;">Knowsley Against Racism is a campaign 
to challenge all forms of racial hatred 
and make Knowsley a safer place in 
which all people can live, work and 
spend their leisure time regardless of 
their background.  The council and its 
partners have launched this campaign as 
part of a strategy to stamp out racism 
in Knowsley.<br />
<br />
</div>
<div style="clear:both;">The campaign was launched at King 
George V playing fields on 23 October 
2005 through a programme of lively and 
family focused activities that 
celebrated diversity, highlighted 
different cultures, and gave out a 
strong anti-racism message.<br />
<br />
</div>
<div style="clear:both;"><h2>Report it</h2>We are asking you to speak out if you 
know of any incidents of racial abuse 
in your area.  Racism is not acceptable 
in Knowsley and will not be tolerated.  
The council and its partners will act 
upon any reports  immediately to 
proactively challenge racist behaviour.<br />
<br />
</div>
<div style="clear:both;"><h2>Get involved</h2>A Multi Agency Racial Harassment Forum 
in Knowsley has been established to 
address racial harassment in the 
borough.  The community of Knowsley is 
represented on this forum through the 
Community Empowerment Network.  To find 
out more call 0151 546 5137.<br />
<br />
Your help is essential if we are to 
beat racism in Knowsley.  We want you 
to get involved and report any 
incidents that you are aware of.  We 
will actively respond to your reports 
and keep you informed of the latest 
developments, and how they will affect 
you.<br />
<br />
</div>
<div style="clear:both;"><h2>Contacts</h2>You can contact Knowsley Council&#039;s 
Corporate Equality and Diversity 
Officer for further information 
(see &#039;who to contact box&#039; below).  You 
can also contact any of the following.  
All calls will be treated in extreme 
confidence.<br />
<br />
Crime Stoppers 0800 555 111<br />
<br />
Police 0151 709 6010<br />
<br />
Knowsley Council&#039;s Violent Crime 
Manager 0151 443 3181 (office hours 
9.00am to 5.00pm)<br />
<br />
Find out more about the Knowsley 
Against Racism Campaign by clicking on 
the link below.<br />
<br />
<a tabindex="326" title="Knowsley Against Racism Campaign" href="/social/againstracism_camp.html">Knowsley Against Racism Campaign</a></div>
